&lt;h1 id="the-risk-of-discovery"&gt;The Risk of Discovery&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;January 2017&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because biographies of famous scientists tend to edit out their mistakes, we underestimate the degree of risk they were willing to take. And because anything a famous scientist did that wasn&amp;rsquo;t a mistake has probably now become the conventional wisdom, those choices don&amp;rsquo;t seem risky either.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>